        <abstract> 
<p>Comments at length on CL’s book [<hi rend="italic">Antiquity of man</hi> (1863)]. CD is "greatly disappointed that you have not given judgment and spoken fairly out what you think about the derivation of species".</p> 
            <p>Lists large number of queries concerning minor points.</p>
            <p>Praises especially the chapters on language and glaciers.</p>
            <p>Comments on the temperature of Africa during the glacial period, especially with regard to the views of Hooker.</p> 
<p>Mentions Owen’s paper on the aye-aye [<hi rend="italic">Rep. BAAS</hi> 32 (1862) pt 2: 114–16].</p> 
        </abstract>
